.TH NOISSH-KEYGEN 1 "2026-06-19" "noissh 0.4.14" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
noissh\-keygen \- ensure a noissh static keypair exists and print its public key
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B noissh\-keygen
.RB [ \-\-key
.IR PATH ]
.br
.B noissh\-keygen \-\-help
.br
.B noissh\-keygen \-\-version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B noissh\-keygen
ensures a long\-term static keypair exists for noissh and prints its public key
line. If the key file is missing it is created (with
.B 0600
permissions); if it already exists, its public key is printed without
regenerating, so the command is safe to run repeatedly.
.PP
The printed line has the form
.RS
.B noissh\-x25519
.I <base64-public-key>
.RE
.PP
Paste that line into a server's
.I authorized_keys
file to authorize this identity. The keypair is the same one the
.BR noissh (1)
client generates on first use, so running this is only necessary when you want
to print or pre\-create the key (for example, to authorize yourself on a server
before your first connection).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-key " PATH"
Use the keypair at
.IR PATH
instead of the default
.RI ( <config>/id ,
where
.I <config>
is
.I ~/.config/noissh
unless overridden by the platform's config directory).
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print usage and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/noissh/id
Default static keypair (private key; created
.BR 0600 ).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The key was printed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (for example, the key file could not be read or created).
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command\-line arguments.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR noissh (1),
.BR noisshd (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The noissh authors. https://github.com/gedigi/noissh
